Date:  0/0/1981
Source:  Loughnan Glossary
Author:  LOUGHNAN
Vol / Page:  11
Edition:
Quote:  broken -mouthed: by its fifth year an adult sheep has erupted eight incisor teeth and is termed full-mouthed. The teeth then begin to deteriorate and the animal steadily becomes broken- or failing-mouthed.
Notes:

